sentences: Radomir Mihailović (Serbian Cyrillic: Радомир Михаиловић; born 13 June  1950), also known as Točak (wheel in English) is a Serbian guitarist.
In 1970, he played frequently in various clubs in Belgium.
Not long after, in 1971 he forms Smak (eng.
Their first full-length, Smak, was released in 1975.
The English version of the album was also released in 1978, called "Black Lady".
Mihailović was born on 13th of July, 1950, in Čačak, Serbia, SFR Yugoslavia.
He started playing various stringed instruments since 5 years old, to finally commit to the guitar at the age of 9.
